column1:
*اذكر يا رب العشمانين 
المنتظرين بلهفة .. اللي مستني نتيجة تحليل او اشعة .. اللي منتظر شغل يأكل منه اسرته ..اللي مستني رسالة مهمة من حد بعيد عنه .. .. البردانة من سقعة الحب المزيف و نفسها تلمس هدب ثوبك .. اللي شرب من مياه ملوثة  و جرب مسكنات كتير و منتظر الشبع الحقيقي .. 
اللي هربان من الدوشة و الزحمة في الدنيا و منتظرك تقعد تتعشي معاه في البيت  .. اللي قاعد بره و دوره جاي في interview .. 
اللي تايهين من بعض و مستنيين الخطوة مين يبدأ و يتكلم .. 
اللي علاقته بيك منعدمة و القيود مانعاه و ماسك في خطيته و مستني تخبط علي بابه .. 
اللي بيحب و خايف يصارح عشان ميتجرحش و مستني  .. اللي مستني تعويض بعد التجربة و اتأخر في السكة و تاه ..
كل بيت فقد شخص وموجوع علي فراقه ..
كل شخص متألم ف جسده من مرض ومستني لمسة شفا منك
اللي مهموم وشايل مشاكل كتير ووحيد مش لاقي حد يتكلم معاه 

هون يا رب كل انتظار  🙏🏼
"اللذي لايخزي منتظروك"

+ صديقك هو قلبك الثاني ، الذي يحسّ بنفس شعورك. يتألم لألمك من أعماقه، ويفرح لفرحك من أعماقه . هو رصيد لكَ من الحب، ورصيد من العون، وبخاصة في وقت الضيق لا يتخلّى عنك. ما أجمل قول سليمان الحكيم في سفر الجامعة : " إثنان خير من واحد. لأن إن وقع أحدهما يُقيمه رفيقه. وويل لمنْ هو وحده إن وقع، إذ ليس ثانٍ يقيمه "، إن الذي لا يقيمك لا يمكن أن يكون صديقك .

column1:
Texts are the shortest day to misunderstanding, they make you read it the way you want to. Not the way they say it.

You can't hear the changes in their breaths when they say how much they miss you.
This smile you can feel when you flirt with you. 
This sigh you get when you say something they wanted to hear. 
You won't be able to hear that tone of " I'm not fighting, I only want a discussion " in a fight.
You won't be capable to listen to their voice vibrations that send you a certain vibe. 

Maybe a text is easier but they never target the heart. 
They always make things harder in fights and colder in love.

column1:
هدية من القلب للقلب...علشان كل اخواتنا واطفالنا اللى بنفقدهم فى مستشفيات الغلابة لان فصائلهم مش متوفرة...قررنا ككنيسة بتخدم المجتمع بطريقة عملية، ان نكسر الضلمة وننور فى وسط مجتمعنا ونبدأ بنفسنا.
علشان كدة جهز نفسك يوم الجمعة الجاية 3 فبراير علشان تشارك معانا فى حملة التبرع بالدم "هدية من القلب للقلب" ...دورك اساسى وفعال ..تعالى وخليك ايجابى...مبادر...ابدأ بنفسك...وكمان شارك الفكرة مع ناس تانية. 
هنكون فى استقبالكم على مدار اليوم من الساعة 10ص حتى الساعة 9م بكنيسة قصر الدوبارة. 
شكرا لمحبتكم 😊
JOIN US 😇😍

column1:
It's quite sad that the people who are closest to you can get so used to you that they no longer see you as a fascinating being. Your wittiness and sense of humor and kindness and achievements and all that makes you who you are becomes unnoticed and not that you should be those things to be noticed, but sometimes you find yourself doubting your own goodness.Sometimes you're filled with your own insecurities and you lose track of what you're worth and what you deserve and it's good to have friends that remind you of what your essence is, where your true beauty exists. It really is disappointing to not have that constant support system because the closer you get to people, the more you see their details,flaws mixed with beauty. That on its own is a reason to be fascinated; for everyone's character adds something to the world. Point is if the people around you don't make you feel like you're worth being loved; then you're hanging out with the wrong crowd and if you're the wrong crowd, be nicer, it helps.

column1:
7abet awassak el yom da (elle howa kan enbare7 technically) 
1- I interviewed people for the first time and it was just plain AMAZING!! I got to meet amazing people who, again, made me believe that u just CANNOT judge a book by its cover and that there is  A WHOLE LOT more to someone than what meets the eye. It was truly a gift to get to sit with them and listen to what they had to say.
2- I shared Nada in using her jacket as an umbrella
3- Youmna we hya betfawet el lafa we b3den to2af b3ed 3an el bus :P xD <3 we b3den edatny kees plastic we da top secret <3 (Rbna y5aleke wAllahy :** )
4- I kept waiting in the pouring rain for 30 mins or more WITH my laptop!!! After missing one bus while I was crossing the street and the missing the one right behind it even though I made a run for it xD but still didn't manage to catch either (LIKE I CROSSED A STREET RUNNING WHILE IT WAS POURING CATS AND DOGS, MAN !! COULDN'T U LOOK AT YOUR MIRROR AND SEE A WET, POOR, UNFORTUNATE HUMAN RUNNING AFTER YOU?!) 
The funny thing is that as I ran after the bus I heard a lady say "ya 3ene" and when I'd missed it she gave me this "m3lesh ya bnty" sympathetic look xD it was really funny
After which I just lost all hope of going home dry in any way and my glasses well ... let's just say they weren't helping me see anything anymore xD (AKA I completely got soaked head to toe xD)  .. we fel wake3 ana kont lessa 7a5ef y3ne men el bard elle kan 3ndy but after tonight am pretty sure eno karar yegeb el sheret men el awel tany xD
4- It's worth mentioning that the rain stopped as soon as I arrived home .. it's like that grey cloud that haunts an unlucky person in cartoons or movies xD it's quite hesterical actually xD

 but all with a good laugh and great company <3

column1:
I am here to tell you that there are people who have never been defeated. They are the ones who never fought. They managed to avoid scars, humiliations, and feelings of helplessness, as well as those moments when even Warriors doubt the existence of God. Such people can say with pride: “I never lost a battle.”On the other hand, they will never be able to say: “I won a battle.”
Not that they care.They live in a universe in which they believe they are invulnerable; they close their eyes to injustices and to suffering; they feel safe because they do not have to deal with the daily challenges faced by those who risk stepping out beyond their own boundaries.”Those who were never defeated seem happy and superior, masters of a truth they never had to lift a finger to achieve. They are always on the side of the strong. They’re like hyenas, who eat only the leavings of lions. They teach their children: “Don’t get involved in conflicts; you’ll only lose. Keep your doubts to yourself and you’ll never have any problems. If someone attacks you, don’t get offended or demean yourself by hitting back. There are more important things in life.
”In the silence of the night, they fight their imaginary battles: their unrealized dreams, the injustices to which they turned a blind eye, the moments of cowardice they managed to conceal from other people—but not from themselves—and the love that crossed their path with a sparkle in its eyes, the love God had intended for them, but Which they lacked the courage to embrace. And they promise themselves: “Tomorrow will be different.”But tomorrow comes and the paralyzing question surfaces in their mind: “What if it doesn’t work out?”And so they do nothing.
 Woe to those who were never beaten! They will never be winners in this life.
by Paulo Coelho - Manuscript Found in Accra

column1:
A man is driving down the road and breaks down near a monastery. He goes to the monastery, knocks on the door, and says, “My car broke down. Do you think I could stay the night?”

The monks graciously accept him, feed him dinner, even fix his car. As the man tries to fall asleep, he hears a strange sound.

The next morning, he asks the monks what the sound was, but they say, “We can’t tell you. You’re not a monk.”

The man is disappointed but thanks them anyway and goes about his merry way.

Some years later, the same man breaks down in front of the same monastery.

The monks accept him, feed him, even fix his car. That night, he hears the same strange noise that he had heard years earlier.

The next morning, he asks what it is, but the monks reply, “We can’t tell you. You’re not a monk.”

The man says, “All right, all right. I’m *dying* to know. If the only way I can find out what that sound was is to become a monk, how do I become a monk?”

The monks reply, “You must travel the earth and tell us how many blades of grass there are and the exact number of sand pebbles. When you find these numbers, you will become a monk.”

The man sets about his task. Forty-five years later, he returns and knocks on the door of the monastery. He says, “I have traveled the earth and have found what you have asked for. There are 145,236,284,232 blades of grass and 231,281,219,999,129,382 sand pebbles on the earth.”

The monks reply, “Congratulations. You are now a monk. We shall now show you the way to the sound.”

The monks lead the man to a wooden door, where the head monk says, “The sound is right behind that door.”

The man reaches for the knob, but the door is locked. He says, “Real funny. May I have the key?”

The monks give him the key, and he opens the door.

Behind the wooden door is another door made of stone.

The man demands the key to the stone door.

The monks give him the key, and he opens it, only to find a door made of ruby.

He demands another key from the monks, who provide it.

Behind that door is another door, this one made of sapphire.

So it went until the man had gone through doors of emerald, silver, topaz, and amethyst.

Finally, the monks say, “This is the last key to the last door.”

The man is relieved to no end.

He unlocks the door, turns the knob, and behind that door he is amazed to find the source of that strange sound.

But I can’t tell you what it is because you’re not a monk

column1: بين اليهود و المجوس............ المسيح طلع من سبط يهوذا لاجلنا كما يقول بولس الرسول ,اما اليهود فلم يستنيروا بذلك الذى اشرق عليهم . لم يكن للمجوس صلة او علاقة بعهود الموعد , و كانوا غرباء عن بركة الاباء , لكنهم سبقوا الشعب الاسرائيلى فى المعرفة و عرفوا دلالة النجم السمائي و لم يجهلوا طبيعة الملك الذى كان فى المذود . لقد حمل المجوس معهم هدايا , بينما الاخرون (اليهود ) تأمروا علية . المجوس سجدوا له , بينما الاخرون طاردوة . المجوس فرحوا عندما وجدوا ذاك الذى كانوا يبحثون عنة . و الاخرون اضطربوا عند ولادته . المجوس قدموا له لبانا كما لاله ، كرموه بذهب ، اشارة الى المقام الملوكى ، و الالم الذى ينتظره بحسب التدبير , اعلنوا عنه بالمر , بينما الاخرون حكموا عليه بالاعدام طوال فترة طفولته .... القديس اغريغوريوس النيسى
column2: below

column1: "اليوم يسمع جميع المحتفلين فى كل المسكونة ترانيم مفرحة . فبأنسان واحد دخل الموت الى العالم ،و بانسان اتى الخلاص . الاول سقط فى الخطية ، و الثانى اقام ذاك الذى سقط . المرأة دافعت عن المرأة .الاولى فتحت الباب للخطية و الثانيه (العذراء ) خدمت الطريق المؤدى للخلاص .الاولى قبلت مشورة الحية و الثانية منحتنا المقدرة على سحق الحية الاولى اتتنا بالخطية بواسطة الاكل من الشجرة و الثانية بواسطة الخشبة اتتنا بالخلاص بدلا من الخطية " القديس اغريغوريوس النيسى

column1: Life is not just about photos, I decided to follow the idea of a friend, in a game called "meeting between friends". the idea is to see who reads a post without pictures. If no one reads my wall, it will be a short experience, but if you read this message, please write a word about both of us. Just a word. For example, a place that makes you think of me, an object, a moment, a restaurant, a coffee, a sport, a movie... and then copy this message on your wall and I'll leave Please don't leave the word if you don't have time to copy the text. It would ruin the pleasure of the game.

column1:
*اذكر يا رب العشمانين 
المنتظرين بلهفة .. اللي مستني نتيجة تحليل او اشعة .. اللي منتظر شغل يأكل منه اسرته ..اللي مستني رسالة مهمة من حد بعيد عنه .. .. البردانة من سقعة الحب المزيف و نفسها تلمس هدب ثوبك .. اللي شرب من مياه ملوثة و جرب مسكنات كتير و منتظر الشبع الحقيقي .. 
اللي هربان من الدوشة و الزحمة في الدنيا و منتظرك تقعد تتعشي معاه في البيت .. اللي قاعد بره و دوره جاي في interview .. 
اللي تايهين من بعض و مستنيين الخطوة مين يبدأ و يتكلم .. 
اللي علاقته بيك منعدمة و القيود مانعاه و ماسك في خطيته و مستني تخبط علي بابه .. 
اللي بيحب و خايف يصارح عشان ميتجرحش و مستني .. اللي مستني تعويض بعد التجربة و اتأخر في السكة و تاه ..
كل بيت فقد شخص وموجوع علي فراقه ..
كل شخص متألم ف جسده من مرض ومستني لمسة شفا منك
اللي مهموم وشايل مشاكل كتير ووحيد مش لاقي حد يتكلم معاه

هون يا رب كل انتظار  🙏🏼
"اللذي لايخزي منتظروك"
